notesStmt.note: Written 7-13 lines per leaf. Mistakes covered over by yellow and red powder smeared on numbers and many lines.
Aṣṭaka 1: leaves 1-12 are unaccented, and in a different hand than the rest. There is slight overlap between these and leaves 20-28, 2-53, which are continuous.
Aṣṭaka 2: title: iti dvitiyāṣṭaka prāraṃbhaḥ samhitā asya idam pustakam bhikambhaṭṭa....likhitam. Ends: Samvat 1874.
Aṣṭaka 3: folio 1A(r) is an unidentified fragment not belonging to this text. Folios 1A and 1B are written by a different hand. Many pages colored in yellow.
Aṣṭaka 6: the beginning and end are in different hands.
